Antennae
relatively short (AnL 
6.35 mm
), individual antennomeres thick, covered with white setae on basal half of scape, on distal tips of antennomeres I–V, distal half of VI, whole VII–VIII, and with blackish setae on IX–XI (
Fig. 7
).

Male genitalia.
Segment 8 (
Figs. 22, 24
) robust and wide, tergite 8 weakly sclerotized, sternite 8 forming from two weakly sclerotised sclerites (= sternal lobes). Sternite 9 (= spiculum gastrale) thin and short, arms longer than apodeme (
Figs. 23–24
). Aedeagus robust, tectum wide with broadly rounded apex, pedon narrower with pointed tip. Apex of tegmen robust, wide, nearly rectangular, apex broadly rounded, densely covered with numerous long setae. Internal sac short (
Figs. 19–21
).
